JAKE FROM STATE FARM
programme.desc: Jake Reed chases Iowa turkeys and successfully takes his first turkey with a bow.

programme.title: RAIN DELAY PART II
programme.desc: Every year Kanas tends to be a successful trip for us. Although starting the hunt with some unfavorable weather was less than idea, we knew once they weather cleared and the birds dried out, they would be fired up. After Shawn and Trent broke the ice with the first birds of the trip, we were ready to get back out there and keep the momentum going.

programme.title: RAIN DELAY PART II
programme.desc: Every year Kanas tends to be a successful trip for us. Although starting the hunt with some unfavorable weather was less than idea, we knew once they weather cleared and the birds dried out, they would be fired up. After Shawn and Trent broke the ice with the first birds of the trip, we were ready to get back out there and keep the momentum going.

programme.title: TRIED AND TRUE
programme.desc: After a long cold winter being cooped up indoors, were always more than ready to kick off turkey season. Since we started traveling years back, one of our very first trips out of state was to Nebraska. Since then we've stuck to where it all started and continue to go back to Nebraska each and every year.

programme.title: RAIN DELAY PART I
programme.desc: With Nebraska being a little tough, we were more than excited to get to KS. This trips' always been one of our best producing in the years past due to the high number of susceptible birds, which typically means there's plenty of opportunity. As long as we can capitalize on these opportunities we know that these next few days in Kansas can be some of the best that we will have all spring.

programme.title: IN THE CHIPS
programme.desc: Ty Wes and Andy have been hunting together for over 20 years and have acquired some prime turkey ground to hunt in Kansas. Opening weekend has proved to be successful in years past and this year was no different as all 3 were able to fill a tag on some incredible hunts.

programme.title: HEADSTRONG
programme.desc: Just like most, we have made this trip our Northern Missouri farm into an annual adventure for the crew and its one we look forward to every year. Not just for the hunting, but for the camaraderie and other extracurricular activities that accompany this trip. Despite many failed attempts success is found and the end of the trip. Trips like these are more about the good times spent with family and friends. The memories made throughout the entire trip are what bring us back. The hunt itself is just an added bonus.

programme.title: IN THE CHIPS
programme.desc: Ty Wes and Andy have been hunting together for over 20 years and have acquired some prime turkey ground to hunt in Kansas. Opening weekend has proved to be successful in years past and this year was no different as all 3 were able to fill a tag on some incredible hunts.

programme.title: HOME GROWN
programme.desc: Its always good to be hunting in our home state of Missouri. Chasing turkeys on properties that we are extremely familiar with tends to result in high success rates and lots of encounters at full draw.

programme.title: HOMEFIELD ADVANTAGE
programme.desc: When we pick up a bow to pursue turkeys, were instantly stacking the odds against us. What makes this type of hunting so exciting is being up against so many different obstacles and overcoming those obstacles in order to find success. This season in Missouri seemed to be hit or miss, but Ty and Wes were able to capitalize on a couple of great opportunities when everything seemed just right.

programme.title: Breaking Tradition
programme.desc: Jake Goodwin and Manny Nativi use non-traditional methods to kill big Iowa gobblers.

programme.title: CLOSEOUT
programme.desc: After a long season in Missouri, Ty travels back to Kansas to try and fill his second Kansas tag during the late part of the season. As breeding season winds down, birds can be tough, but if you catch one in the right mood the hunting can be great!

programme.title: GRASS ROOTS
programme.desc: Spring turkey season for Mike this year was split up by a much welcomed trip of a lifetime to Alaska. After spending 17 days on Kodiak Island hunting Brown Bears, he missed out on most of the Missouri season, but was anxious to get back to the lower 48 and finish out the season strong.

programme.title: Bass Fishing with a Simple Walmart Bass Fishing Rod, Reel and Tackle Setup
programme.desc:
Need a quick and easy bass rod and reel setup? So did I! While out of town in Moultrie, Georgia for business, I forgot my bass rod and tackle at home, so I ran to the local Walmart and bought just what I needed for a great price. Walk with me as I pick out which bass fishing rod I prefer and why, than the lures I think would work best for bass while here in Moultrie, Georgia.
After purchasing my bass fishing rod and bass tackle from Walmart for a great price, I head on over to a local pond near the hotel I am staying at in Moultrie, Georgia. I than set up my new Lew's Speed Stick rod by attaching the Abu Garcia reel I bought to it. Then I string my Spiderwire braided fishing line through my new pole and attach some 20 pound mono to the end. After that I tie a size 3/0 Mustad offset hook to my line, put on split slide weights, and I am ready for the lure! I bought two different types of rubber worms. Purple Powerbaits and Watermelon Yum Dingers.
I am ready to catch some bass! On Day 1, I used the Watermelon worms and caught three gorgeous Georgia Bass! On Day 2 I tried to switch up to the purple and didn't get a single hit. Switched back to the Watermelon worms and caught a bass almost instantly!

Hunting the Rut in Mississippi - Part 1

"We were invited by the owners of Conviction Outdoors to come hunt their gorgeous rolling hills on almost 200 acres of private family land. They stayed in the cabin on the property as well which was hand built by the owner himself. Absolutely gorgeous! We were so blessed to have had this opportunity and we enjoyed the property, food, and fellowship very much! To have been invited back was icing on the cake!"

programme.title: 200 Disabled Veterans go Deep Sea Fishing in the Gulf!
programme.desc:
We were invited by Iron Men Outdoor Ministries to attend their Annual Deep Sea Fishing with Disabled Veterans trip. These two days consisted of a banquet to raise money and honor all of the disabled veterans that were invited on the fishing trip, as well as a day on the water, deep sea fishing on several boats!
There ended up being 200 disabled veterans fishing! There were 20 total boats that took these men and women fishing! Three of these boats were 90 foot fishing charter vessels, and the rest were smaller charter boats. The total number of fish caught exceeded 2000! The total number of fish kept was about 1600!
This entire trip was amazing to say the least! Being asked to film and collect content of what it is that Iron Men Ministries does, as well as to capture these disabled vets having a blast catching fish, was such an honor and so humbling! We are already counting down the days till the next one!
Here are all the ways to connect with Iron Men Outdoors: Website: https://www.ironmenoutdoorministries.com/ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/IMOM2013 Festus Potee: https://www.facebook.com/festus.potee

programme.title: Seared Sturgeon
programme.desc: Fresh from the Lake Winnebago system in east-central Wisconsin, Lake Sturgeon are a rare delicacy. More common than not they are smoked, but what if we told you there's this other way to prepare sturgeon that will leave your guests in disbelief? Try this awesome recipe and you won't be disappointed!

programme.title: Venison Backstrap w/Fire Melted Bleu Cheese and Bacon
programme.desc: Alakan Sitka Deer backstraps grilled over mesquite lump coal and drizzled over by fire melted blue cheese and crumbled smoked bacon. Try this with any venison backstrap and savor every bite!

programme.title: Cedar Plank Great Lakes King Salmon
programme.desc: Salmon is hard to cook wrong, but it's also hard to cook just right. This is our favorite recipe of all the different ways to cook salmon and it is super easy. Cedar, smoke, Rosemary and Thyme. Bring on the compliments after you serve this to your guests!

programme.title: Venison Hangover Burger w/Quail Eggs
programme.desc: This is one of our absolute best burger recipe we've ever served up. We use whitetail venison for this video and pair it up with grilled sweet onion, Nueske's smoked bacon, smokehouse cheddar and provolone, along with a trio of sunny-side up quail eggs on top. Oh, and let's not forget a little bit of barbecue sauce to dress it up a little more. Perfection in a toasted bun!

programme.title: Fried Panfish Tacos w/Chipotle Mayo
programme.desc: Hands down one of the best ways to prepare a fresh catch of bluegills, crappie and perch. In this episode we use a half-dozen 10-12" crappies we caught in the spring time out of a cold deep Northern Wisconsin lake. We mix up a Chipotle Mayo sauce, mix up fresh green and red cabbage sliced thinly and add a couple clean wedges of fresh ripe avocado with a side of black beans. You're going to love this recipe!

programme.title: A Treestand Over Your Garden
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri goes on a hunt for Axis Deer and then prepares a Seared Axis Deer Carpaccio with Arugula, Capers, and shaved Parmesan. Bri wraps the episode up with her take on a Shrimp & Shishito Pepper Taco recipe.

programme.title: Ropin' Gators and for Korean BBQ
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri gets a chance to go on an airboat looking for gators. Then she prepares Korean BBQ Alligator with Ginger Sesame Rice. To wrap things up, Bri puts together a Buffalo Alligator Taco recipe.

programme.title: Swamp Bacon
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri goes off on a hunt for hog in a way she did not expect. When Bri gets back to camp, she cooks up her take on Wild Boar Porchetta with salt and vinegar potatoes on the side. Then to wrap things up, Bri puts together a Chipotle Pineapple Axis Deer Taco recipe.

programme.title: Stag Party
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri goes on a hunt for Red Stag. When Bri gets back to camp, she grinds up red stag meat to create a red stag burger with bacon jam and cheese. Then to wrap things up, Bri puts together a Moroccan Stag Taco recipe.

programme.title: Dan Dan Ram
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri goes on a long day of hunting for a ram. The next morning, Bri puts together a Ram Spicy Dan Dan Noodles dish. Then to wrap things up, Bri creates a Dan Dan Taco recipe.

programme.title: Squirrel!
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri goes on the hunt for squirrels and takes her shot at quail. After the hunt, Bri puts together a Buttermilk Fried Squirrel and Quail recipe. Then to wrap things up, Bri puts together a Breakfast Taco recipe.

programme.title: Midnight Gigging for Tacos
programme.desc: In this episode, Chef Bri gets back on the water and goes after Tilapia. This time, she is fishing from the airboat at night using lights and a fishing gig pole. Back at the camp, Bri cooks a Cornmeal Crusted Tilapia with Mandarin Oranges, Brown Butter Sauce, Toasted Hazelnuts, and Arugula. Then to wrap things up, Bri creates a Tilapia Taco recipe.

programme.title: Diving with Troy and Hercules and Cooking
programme.desc: Jeff lets Troy and Hercules dive and cook up some fish!

programme.title: Cranberry Elk Stuffed Acorn Squash
programme.desc: Watch Chef Shelly utilize wild elk in a recipe for Cranberry Elk Stuffed Acorn Squash. She uses an interesting spice combination to create Moroccan spices for this fall dish. Perfect for this time of year. Plus she shares tips on how to prepare this a day in advance then bring together as a fun dinner party idea.

programme.title: Espresso Antelope Tenderloin
programme.desc: Antelope tenderloin is one of the leanest and easiest proteins to cook. In this episode Chef Shelly pan sears her antelope tenderloins with an espresso spice rub. Another interesting tip she shares is about which vegetable pairs perfectly with coffee rubs and why.

programme.title: Grouse Alfredo
programme.desc: Chef Shelly shows an easy recipe for Alfredo using wild harvested Spruce Grouse. Especially comforting meal for when you're home alone while your spouse is out hunting. In addition she makes a homemade mayo for her Caesar Dressing that's so healthy & easy it'll replace store bought.

programme.title: Balsamic Marinated Elk

programme.title: Blackened Salmon
programme.desc: Wild salmon is the star of this episode. Chef Shelly explains how & why she pairs specific side dishes with her Cajun spiced Blackened Salmon recipe. These sides make the dish well rounded with easy composed flavors that compliment each other. Tune in and learn her cooking tips & tricks.

programme.title: Parmesan Crusted Pheasant
programme.desc: Chef Shelly shares family stories while showing how to increase moisture & tenderness in dryer game cuts like this UNIQUE recipe for Pheasant Parmesan. She shows her easy quick brine technique. Then the side dish she pairs with it is her Bloody Mary Polenta. You'll want this recipe in your weekly meal rotation, trust me!

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #1 - Robbie Kroger "In the Blood"
programme.desc: What is Blood Origins? Robbie Kroger tells us about his philosophy on what Blood Origins means and relates it to his story. A South African native, he has come to the United States and is looking to his past to learn more about what hunting meant to him and his family for generations.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #2 - Keith Polk & Lake Pickle "Threaded"
programme.desc: Everyone has a story… For Lake & Keith, it is one of mentorship, lifelong friendship, and a passion for sharing their love of hunting with younger generations. Through a program bringing the hunting experience to younger generations, they came to know more about their love of the outdoors and being a role model. The tradition then lived on through their experiences like many other traditions in the hunting community.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #3 - Ryan "Koup" Kuperus "Giants"
programme.desc: Ryan "Koup" Kuperus is a retired USMC Gunnery Sergeant. After a devastating Humvee rollover accident, his femur and back were both broken. The nature of his accident and experiences overseas left him searching for answers on how to adjust to life at home. The outdoors and hunting provided him with an escape. Now, he works on engaging other veterans and people going through experiences like his to hunting and the outdoors. Using the experiences of nature and hunting traditions, he works to give others the healing he found in the peacefulness of the wilderness.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #4 - Craig Corsi "Giants"
programme.desc: Craig Corsi lives the hunting life dedicated to the outdoors. A retired USMC 1st Sergeant, the path Corsi has chosen for himself is based on the tenants of family, hunting, and dedication to the outdoors. Through his business and lifestyle, he can invest in others and bring more experiences to those around him looking to understand the hunting tradition.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #5 - Cuz Strickland "Heart"
programme.desc: As one of the originators, Cuz Strickland has the insight to tell a story more rooted in hunting and tradition than most. He was focused from experiences at a young age on how hunting and humanity came together. He aims to always make that experience available to young people. He wants the hunters of tomorrow to see the outdoors and love of the forests from a lense of understanding and respect.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #8 - Leonard Bentz "Fathers"
programme.desc: Your story is likely unique to you, just as my own story is probably unlike yours.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #12 - Derek Harris "Memories"
programme.desc: From an early age Derek was raised to be a different breed of hunter. It wasn't all about the kill. His dad instilled in him that being outdoors is an experience. Being outdoors is about making memories and relationships with others. He would take these same values and instill them into his little brother. As he matured Derek took this one step further, by becoming a professional outfitter in New Mexico, and took it as a profession to take others hunting and into the outdoors to make their own memories

programme.title: Repeat Success
programme.desc: Skyler and Clayton typically kick off their turkey season in Kansas each year hunting the early archery season. Having hunted the same properties for the past several years, they typically have a great idea of where to start and after going back to back last year, they are excited to try and pull it off again.

programme.title: Back to Back
programme.desc: After a couple years of lower than usual turkey numbers, things seem to be on the rebound as Trent and Derek take to the field for the opening week of Kansas turkey season. Timing could not be any more perfect as the birds are fired up and in the perfect mood!

programme.title: 2 in 2
programme.desc: To start his season, Shawn heads to western Kansas to hunt with Midwest Land Group's Cole Shew. Having had success hunting deer in the past with Cole, Shawn was optimistic of what the week would hold and it did not disappoint!

programme.title: Just in Time
programme.desc: After a couple days of hunting and several close calls, Mike & the guys make a move to try to get in front of a group of birds mid-morning. As they scramble to set up, the birds round the bend and the guys are forced to hit the dirt to avoid being caught moving.

programme.title: Tempermental
programme.desc: The opening week of Missouri season has dealt Mike some very stubborn birds. Sometimes you can do everything just right and it doesn't seem to matter. 4 days into the season, after several heart-breaks, he finally finds a bird that wants to play rough and another that doesn't want to leave!

programme.title: Turf and Surf
programme.desc: It can be so frustrating when you are sure it's going to finally come together and the birds decide to do something completely different. On the flip side, all of that can change in the blink of an eye. After several close calls, Ty & Andy catch exactly the break they were looking for allowing them to tag out and head to the lake to fish!

programme.title: On A String
programme.desc: Each and every spring Ty makes it a point to spend some time hunting with his father and his daughter, but it's a rarity that he's able to hunt with them both at the same time. This year though, they were able to get out twice and the second time out was a hunt they won't soon forget!

programme.title: Payback
programme.desc: It seems like the last few springs have been a test with a declining turkey population and decoy shy birds. After many failed attempts, we finally came across the rights birds to commit to the decoys. We are hopeful that this is the turnaround that we have been looking for.

programme.title: Mixed Bag
programme.desc: Kicking off every turkey season in Kansas is something that Ty and Andy always look forward to. This year, however, was a little different in years past. They hunted hard, but failed to get birds to commit to the decoys during the early season. After finding some success in Missouri, they head back to KS for a shot at redemption.

programme.title: 90+ Turkeys In Our Decoys?!? (My First Nebraska Gobbler!)
programme.desc: We start off our Turkey season in Nebraska with friend, Cody Freeze! Shawn, Trent, and Derek all have tags in their pocket and both Shawn and Trent have never harvested a Gobbler in the state! With it being the earliest season opening sometimes the birds like to stay grouped up which can make for some very interesting hunts! See how the HB guys get it done with these tough conditions!

programme.title: Opening Day Kansas Archery Gobbler! (Perfect Shot!!)
programme.desc: Clayton and Skyler always start their turkey season off in Kansas. With the early Archery season it makes for a great advantage if the birds are acting right. This year they are looking for redemption for a rough season the year prior and man did it come together perfectly! Tag along on this intense Archery Turkey Hunt!

programme.title: Texas Gobbler Comes Screaming In & Beats Up My Decoy! (First Texas Rio)
programme.desc: Mike, Nate, Joey, Joel, and Brandon all head to Texas to meet up with their friend Caleb to try and harvest their first ever Texas Turkey's! After some unexpected weather it throws the Turkey's into a little funk that might make this trip harder than expected. Follow along as the guys test their luck on some Texas Rio's and maybe even a little Large Mouth Bass competition along the way!

programme.title: Chasing Turkeys & Giant Sheds in Colorado! (My Biggest Shed Ever!!)
programme.desc: Mike & Brandon head back to Colorado to meet up with their good friends Tony and Pete & Will. They have Deer and Turkey hunted with them over the past couple years and it has become a tradition to continue to come back. The turkeys are always fun to chase, but equally as exciting is the post season scouting for deer and picking up some Giant Colorado Whitetail Sheds!

programme.title: The Perfect Turkey Season: Filling 3 Tags with a Bow
programme.desc: Shawn and Rex have one of their best Archery Turkey seasons in Missouri filling 3 out of their 4 tags! Starting off opening day with an incredible hunt where Rex's bird smashes the decoy before Rex makes a perfect shot with a wild recovery. Then they set out to keep the hot streak going the rest of the season with two more incredible hunts and perfect archery shots on big mature Missouri Gobblers.

programme.title: Turkey Tag Out With A Bow! Some Of The Best Turkey Hunts I've Ever Had!
programme.desc: Mike has another unforgettable Turkey season in Missouri tagging out on two incredible Archery turkey hunts! Starting off with a close call he then follows up quickly with one wild hunt where he makes a perfect shot on a big mature gobbler that is on top of his decoy! After that it's a late morning gobbler that comes screaming in and Mike connects with him to fill his final tag!

programme.title: Completed the Spring Slam!! (Turkey, Morel Mushrooms, Deer Shed, & Crappie!)
programme.desc: To finish off the Missouri 3 Peat Rex connects with a gobbler when all had seemed to go wrong. To top it off he completes the Spring Slam by finding Morel Mushrooms, Finding a Deer Shed, and catching some Crappie! Great way to finish off the Missouri Turkey Season!

programme.title: Kansas Kickoff pt. 3
programme.desc: It's a gorgeous Kansas morning in early April and the Heartland Bowhunter crew are having no trouble finding gobblers.

programme.desc: Season 7 of Full Strut

programme.desc: Legends of the Outdoors Hall of Famer, Phillip Vanderpool, introduces two new kids to the Outdoors at Triple H Outfitters in Kansas.

programme.title: Slow down for more birds
programme.desc:
You set the pace in the field, and if you're in a rush so is your dog. That means less time in a scent cone and more missed birds.
Scott Linden of Wingshooting USA TV shows you how, and explains why, you should dial things down a bit when it comes to covering a field or covert.
If you want more tips on dog training and bird hunting, go to: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Hunting dog tailgate exam, part one
programme.desc:
Your best hunting partner needs some TLC ... especially after a hunt. wingshooting USA TV host Scott Linden provides the first part of three, helping you check him from nose tip to tail and ensure he's healthy, safe, and ready to go the next day.
Today, it's all about your dog's coat. We'll cover why it's important to get him off the ground, how "training" for the exam is critical, and what to look for from injuries to parasites. Your dog will stay healthier, well-rested, and ready to go the next day.
You'll also see some fun and exciting bird hunting footage from a hunt where the tailgate exam became crucial.

programme.title: Take a newcomer hunting - here's how
programme.desc:
Safety first, but then what? Author and TV host Scott Linden outlines some ways to encourage, motivate, and then help a new hunter on their first hunt.
From weather to shooting tips, to interacting with the dog, and what really counts on the hunt, Scott offers suggestions to ensure everyone has fun.
For more tips on hunting, dog training, and finding places to go: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Identify your best prospect for a new hunter
programme.desc:
Picking the right new hunting partner is an art and a science ... and while there's no wrong way, some ways are righter than others. Author/TV host Scott Linden outlines some tips on finding the right person, how to set expectations, and what to tell them - and show them - before you make "the ask."
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: The new-hunter best recruiter is your dog!
programme.desc:
Who doesn't love hunting dogs? The magic of their performance, excitement, and the adrenaline rush of a flush! One easy way to start a new hunter is to invite them to help train your dog.
Simple, short, convenient - there's no downside. And who wouldn't appreciate a little help with dog training?
Plus, some cool footage of a hunt with excellent dog works.
For more on starting a hunter, finding places to hunt, and dog training, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com.

programme.title: Ideas for finding new places to hunt
programme.desc:
Find upland birds on waterfowl production areas, and more tips on accessing public hunting areas are two of the topics ... as well as a great place to headquarter: Huron, South Dakota.
Watch some exciting bird hunting footage, too.
Find more information at www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Tailgate exam, part 2: wheels
programme.desc:
Part two covers your dog's "wheels," his feet. Enure a fantastic hunt tomorrow by keeping his feet healthy and injury-free with these step-by-step, toe-by-toe instructions.
Geet the entire exam in written form at HappyJackInc.com.

programme.title: Be nice, see where it gets you
programme.desc:
Walk-in hunting spots are not always easy to find. Here's an example of how to find them and the bonuses you might find along the way.
From hunting with a pro baseball player, to finding a black pheasant, to discovering new public-access spots in Huron, SD, there's a few lessons here.
Plus, some fun footage of a South Dakota pheasant hunt.
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Peak performance on Day Two: feed your dog strategically
programme.desc:
In the first 20 days of this season, my wirehair Flick had already hunted over 200 miles. He still scratches the RV door every morning, eager for another day of chukar chasing and quail quests.
I manage to keep up (mostly) with coffee and pain reliever. Flick, on the other paw, gets his stamina from Dr. Tim's dog food.
If your dog hunts multiple days in a row, it might be worth a look at how important food is to his performance. I asked Doctor Tim Hunt to share his thoughts on that, but first, a hunting story.

programme.title: Tailgate exam, Part 3: His steering wheel
programme.desc:
Okay, we've checked his body, his feet. But the tailgate exam isn't over until you've checked a dog's head – the steering wheel of your hunting machine. Like your truck, you're not getting very far without one! Put off that tall cold one for a couple more minutes. You'll have a fully-functioning hunting partner for the next day … and you won't die of thirst!
In this video, I'll show you where to look, what to look for and why ... and also how to remedy most common issues that might kibosh your next day's hunt, from getting stuff out of eyes and ears, to ensuring weeds and crud stay outta those places and more!
I'll take you step-by-step through all the deep, dark places that harbor danger and irritation on your dog's head so he's ready and rested for the next day's hunt.
And if you need remedies for any of the problems outlined, you can find them at www.happyjackinc.com.

programme.title: Get high, become a better bird hunter
programme.desc:
Not like that! I mean, boost your altitude - even just a bit - and you'll be able to keep a closer eye on your dog. If you're paying attention, you'll have a crucial half-second extra to get ready for a safe, sure shot.
I'll show you how - what you might use to get "up there" a little, what to look for in your dog's behavior, and why it's worth the effort.

programme.title: What's in my vest ... and why
programme.desc:
"Don't leave home without" is more than a cliche' from a TV commercial. What should you take on your next bird hunt, for you and your dog? Here's some advice on critical stuff, and what you might leave home ... without jeopardizing your safety or comfort - or you're dog's!
Somewhere in my personal vest is everything I need to shoot as well as possible (no smart remarks, please), stay found or get found, keep my dog safe and healthy, and help me survive a night or two in an emergency.
I'll show you all of it, and how to keep it from getting lost somewhere in the middle of nowhere!

programme.title: Your dog hurts - here's why
programme.desc:
I seem to be getting a lot of related questions since the season ended – most about aches and pains in our four-footed hunting buddies. And us!
The difference is, dogs won't show it like we do, with gripes and limping, complaints and wincing. They are way too loyal and hard working. It's why we love 'em.
You might already know this, but veterinarians tell me dogs seldom show pain. What they do, is slow down. Their pace in the field drags, they're slow to get out of their crate.
Maybe they won't jump onto your tailgate or training table.
That's probably arthritis, and it affects most dogs over eight years old. But here's the scary part: twenty percent of dogs show signs as early as one year old.
In this video, I'll show you how to prevent arthritis, manage it if your dog already has it, and what to avoid so he doesn't get it prematurely!

programme.title: Fuel your bird dog's peak performance ... but NOT with carbs!
programme.desc:
We hunt to watch our dogs work. So, stand by for plenty of that. But first, let me relate my last season. I tracked Flick's mileage. He averaged twenty-five miles a day, over almost fifty days in the field. I'm a lousy shooter, and okay trainer … so I'll attribute his stamina to my dumb luck, and his performance dog food.
If you want to watch your dog in the field day after day, heed some of the advice I got from Doctor Tim Hunt, a veterinarian, sled dog racer, and developer of the food Flick eats. He says the fuel you put in your dog directly impacts his ability to hunt hard, especially on a long hunting trip. He should know. His food has powered a bunch of Iditarod winners … and my guy Flick.
In this video, you'll learn what the key ingredients are in a dog food, how they work, and why. Hint: the most important component in your dog food is probably NOT what you think it is.

programme.title: Bird dog training: one (baby) step at a time
programme.desc: Dogs learn in a linear fashion, so in this video Scott shows you how important it is to break a complex task into smaller pieces. Training one piece at a time ensures a compliant, happy, peak-performing hunting buddy.

BEONDTV is a Los Angeles-based broadcast and digital media network with a wide variety of original programming curated by Emmy award-winning journalists and content creators.
Wild Ones - S01:E02 - Fastest
programme.desc: The fastest? The explosive sprinting cheetah? The mighty kangaroo? The horned and leaping wildebeest? The powerful and sure-footed horse? Or the swift-footed pronghorn? Which is the fastest over land?

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E03 - Biggest
programme.desc: The Biggest? An Elephant? A Giraffe? A Hippopotamus? Or the humpback whale which is three times longer than the tallest giraffe and weighs more than a dozen hippos. But which is the biggest of them all?

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E04 - Smartest
programme.desc: Are animals smart? You bet. But which is the smartest of them all? The socially complex chimpanzee? The inventive bolas spider? The architectural termite? The curious dolphin? Or the inimitable octopus?

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E11 - Naturally Different
programme.desc: The Shetland Islands: home to 20,000 humans, one million birds and the smallest horse in the world. Then on to an area known to the locals as the Centre of the World in South Eastern province of Kazakhstan. From there we will go to the Yellow Mountains in Central China often called The Venice of China.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E12 - Naturally Vibrant
programme.desc: South Moravia in the Czech Republic is home to a wide variety of beautiful orchids. From there we go to the Caribbean to Cuba with its unbelievably beautiful vistas contrasted with brutal cock fighting. From Cuba we travel to Fiji in the Pacific Ocean – often considered to be a true paradise on Earth.

programme.title: Sasquatch Mountain Man - S04:E06 - Trapping Show
programme.desc: Laramy honors the history of the mountain man by trapping for beaver in the lower rockies.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E06 - Princess Diana's Legacy
programme.desc: Reflecting on Diana's legacy, this show delves into what Princess Diana left behind after her sudden passing - the impression she left on her children, the royal family, and the people who loved her. The young princes drew admiration with their demeanor at her funeral, but many questioned how their bond with Prince Charles would be moving forward.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E03 - Operation Yellowstone
programme.desc: In Region 5, wardens ride a jet boat up the Yellowstone River, keeping an eye on fly fishing guides and stumbling upon a boat mishap. After that, they head to Region 1 for some shooting practice.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E04 - Operation Antelope Dummy
programme.desc: With the number of Pronghorn antelopes dropping, the Wardens in Region 7 set up a decoy sting right before the season kicks off, but the major issue turns out to be people trespassing on opening day. Meanwhile, Region 4 Warden Bryan Golie gets a call about a possible poaching incident.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E06 - Exploration Camp
programme.desc: The guys continue to push down river. Exhausted and starving, the brothers have barely enough energy to set camp. The guys discover is that sign is plentiful and the topography lends itself to moose habitat.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E07 - Prayer Point
programme.desc: By the third day of moving along the river, everyone really needed a hunting camp to lift their spirits and keep pushing towards the goal of taking down a big bull. Tensions ran high and for the first time, the brothers confessed they were at a loss on how to proceed.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E01 - Living with Space
programme.desc: How do astronauts cope with living in space? The unique environment, the lack of taste in their food and the smell of canned air all contribute to the stresses of living and working in space.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E02 - Atmosphere
programme.desc: Climate change and pollution are having dire consequences for the atmosphere of our planet, this episode updates the latest technology and science looking into the health of our air.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E05 - Delta Prison Rescue Operation
programme.desc: In 1989, CIA operative Kurt Muse was imprisoned at the notorious Carcel Modelo in Panama for his role in organizing radio transmissions against dictator Manuel Noriega. That December, an elite group of the US Delta Force breached the roof of the prison, and one of the most daring close quarter battle operations in history began. From the dramatic helicopter crash and wounding of several Delta operators to the extraction of the entire team by the 5th Infantry Division, this is prime material for CQB analysis. In this episode, CQB recreates the raid, focusing on the “sub-second” reflexes of the Delta Force team from the moment they entered the prison to their extraction from the roof of the prison by an MH-6 “Little Bird” helicopter.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E06 - Snipers and Scout
programme.desc: Joint Task Force Two (JTF 2) is the elite Canadian Forces Special Operations unit responsible for a broad range of missions, including counter-terrorism and armed assistance to other government departments. Highly secretive, JTF 2 and its predecessor, the Canadian Airborne Regiment, have been deployed in hotspots around the world from Haiti to Bosnia. This episode focuses on the legendary JTF sniper teams and their use in Afghanistan alongside the British SAS and the US Delta Force at “the sharp end of the spear.” A book written by an ex-JTF member explains how, in 2006, both the Pentagon and the British Foreign Office noted the instrumental role that JTF 2 played in the rescue of the British and Canadian Christian Peacemaker Team held hostage in Iraq. Unique in look, the FN P90 personal defense weapon, used by JTF 2 soldiers and special police around the world, will be highlighted in this program.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E02 - Meateaters
programme.desc: Papua New Guinea Pt2. Jim brings meat to the local village while Corey explores leech infested swamps looking for the local deer. Local villagers tell Jim of a remote area 400 miles away where buffalo roam.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E07 - William And Kate Into The Future
programme.desc: From a regular student to a royal girlfriend, Kate Middleton has transformed into a real-life princess. In less than ten years, this everyday girl with a normal background captured her prince's heart and is now on track to become the future Queen of England.

programme.desc: This show offers a captivating look into the extraordinary life of one of the 20th century's most fascinating women, seen through an American lens. It features clips from the auction where her dresses were sold.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E05 - Operation Cascade
programme.desc: The Upper Missouri River is a top spot for trout fishing and rafting. In Region 4's Cascade district, there's a buzz around a strange camper on private property. In Region 7, they're busy doing water safety inspections.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E06 - Operation Blackfoot
programme.desc: Wardens in Region 2 are checking out a Tip Mont report about several elk down in an area known for grizzlies. When they get there, one elk and the suspect aren't around. Meanwhile, wardens in Region 7 are dealing with gunfire during a decoy sting operation.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E08 - King Of The Tundra
programme.desc: Casey sees a huge bull on the other side of the river and takes it down about 10 yards from the water. Then, another bull comes up the river towards the fallen one. Casey and this bull face off, staring each other down from opposite sides of the river.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E09 - The Day After
programme.desc: After taking down a huge bull, Chris and Casey manage to cut up the 1500-pound moose just as night is about to set in. They then set up a meat storage solution to keep the food good for the rest of their trip.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E03 - Flight Status
programme.desc: The latest updates on The New space hardware about to launch us into the next generation of space flight some rockets and capsules are on time others not so fortunate.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E04 - Invasion Mars
programme.desc: The EXO Mars and Curiosity continue their scientific discoveries as we prepare The New missions both robotic and manned to the Red planet Mars.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E07 - S.W.A.T.
programme.desc: In 1968, a new form of military policing was being developed in a rural area north of Los Angeles. The Los Angeles Police Department sent an observer to this unit, and he, in turn, took this knowledge back to the LAPD. This contributed to the development of the department’s first Special Weapons and Tactics (S.W.A.T.) team. This CQB episode takes an historical journey to examine how this incident affected and changed police tactics around the world. Using CQB’s trademark “sub-second” analysis, the program also looks at how police S.W.A.T. teams train, plan and equip themselves for the challenges of urban combat. The dramatization of a 1980s S.W.A.T. siege of a gang safe-house demonstrates the complicated challenge of protecting innocent people who might be caught in the line of fi re, as well as the specifics of the squad’s training regimen, how they communicated, and the special equipment they used.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E08 - Hunting Sarajevo Snipers
programme.desc: The Bosnian War was an extraordinarily complex event, with many layers of military involvement including NATO forces, national militaries, irregular paramilitary forces, mujahedeen revolutionaries, private security companies, and international intelligence personnel. One tactic in particular struck fear into the hearts of the military and civilians alike: the use of snipers positioned in high buildings. This edition of CQB investigates this specific combat technique and how it was countered by opposing forces. Taking viewers inside a “sniper‘s den,” the program explains how this tactic was so successfully used by rebel forces – and how traditional military techniques evolved to combat it.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E03 - End Game
programme.desc: Papua New Guinea Pt3. Jim and Corey split up and search for buffalo. Jim, unable to reach Corey by radio, hears several shots from Corey's direction and heads out to search for his friend.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E11 - Royal Children Prince William and Prince Harry
programme.desc: Two young men who have had to cope with extraordinarily challenging events and circumstances as, together, they have gone on to change the face of the British royal family and carve meaningful roles for themselves in the modern world. Made in 1999 two years after the death of their mother, Princess Diana, this original and touching documentary examines the lives of the royal princes, the legacy of their mother, the responsibilities of being a royal - and what the future holds for them.

Made in 1999 two years after the death of their mother, Princess Diana, this original and touching documentary examines the lives of the royal princes, the legacy of their mother, the responsibilities of being a royal - and what the future holds for them.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E08 - Princess Diana The Uncrowned Queen
programme.desc: This show offers a captivating look into the extraordinary life of one of the 20th century's most fascinating women, seen through an American lens. It features clips from the auction where her dresses were sold.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E05 - Operation Cascade
programme.desc: The Upper Missouri River is a top spot for trout fishing and rafting. In Region 4's Cascade district, there's a buzz around a strange camper on private property. In Region 7, they're busy doing water safety inspections.

programme.title: Wardens - S01:E06 - Operation Blackfoot
programme.desc: Wardens in Region 2 are checking out a Tip Mont report about several elk down in an area known for grizzlies. When they get there, one elk and the suspect aren't around. Meanwhile, wardens in Region 7 are dealing with gunfire during a decoy sting operation.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E08 - King Of The Tundra
programme.desc: Casey sees a huge bull on the other side of the river and takes it down about 10 yards from the water. Then, another bull comes up the river towards the fallen one. Casey and this bull face off, staring each other down from opposite sides of the river.

programme.title: Dropped - S01:E09 - The Day After
programme.desc: After taking down a huge bull, Chris and Casey manage to cut up the 1500-pound moose just as night is about to set in. They then set up a meat storage solution to keep the food good for the rest of their trip.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E03 - Flight Status
programme.desc: The latest updates on The New space hardware about to launch us into the next generation of space flight some rockets and capsules are on time others not so fortunate.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E04 - Invasion Mars
programme.desc: The EXO Mars and Curiosity continue their scientific discoveries as we prepare The New missions both robotic and manned to the Red planet Mars.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E07 - S.W.A.T.
programme.desc: In 1968, a new form of military policing was being developed in a rural area north of Los Angeles. The Los Angeles Police Department sent an observer to this unit, and he, in turn, took this knowledge back to the LAPD. This contributed to the development of the department’s first Special Weapons and Tactics (S.W.A.T.) team. This CQB episode takes an historical journey to examine how this incident affected and changed police tactics around the world. Using CQB’s trademark “sub-second” analysis, the program also looks at how police S.W.A.T. teams train, plan and equip themselves for the challenges of urban combat. The dramatization of a 1980s S.W.A.T. siege of a gang safe-house demonstrates the complicated challenge of protecting innocent people who might be caught in the line of fi re, as well as the specifics of the squad’s training regimen, how they communicated, and the special equipment they used.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E08 - Hunting Sarajevo Snipers
programme.desc: The Bosnian War was an extraordinarily complex event, with many layers of military involvement including NATO forces, national militaries, irregular paramilitary forces, mujahedeen revolutionaries, private security companies, and international intelligence personnel. One tactic in particular struck fear into the hearts of the military and civilians alike: the use of snipers positioned in high buildings. This edition of CQB investigates this specific combat technique and how it was countered by opposing forces. Taking viewers inside a “sniper‘s den,” the program explains how this tactic was so successfully used by rebel forces – and how traditional military techniques evolved to combat it.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E03 - End Game
programme.desc: Papua New Guinea Pt3. Jim and Corey split up and search for buffalo. Jim, unable to reach Corey by radio, hears several shots from Corey's direction and heads out to search for his friend.

programme.title: 10 Inch Hero
programme.desc: An artist gets a job at a beachside sandwich shop, where she hangs out with a techie, a flirt, a rocker, a hippie, and a Wiccan.

programme.title: Alien Trespass
programme.desc: After crash landing on the outskirts of a desert town, an alien enlists the help of a local waitress to recapture a monster that has escaped the wreckage of his spaceship in this affectionate, knowing, hilarious send-up of a genreís sillier past.

programme.title: Eavesdrop
programme.desc: Ensemble drama about conversations overheard in a bistro: two chess players see unfolding dramas, a couple on an uncomfortable blind date, a crumbling marriage, and film-noir fans that think they're witnessing a real-life murder.

programme.title: Citizen Duane
programme.desc: CITIZEN DUANE is a comedy/drama about Duane Balfour a teen-aged Don Quixote born into a family of spectacular failure. What starts as a simple schoolyard rivalry snowballs out of control when Duane decides to run for mayor of the tiny town of Ridgeway. If Duane is to succeed, he must not only overcome the powerful incumbents, but also his own inadequacies, public perception, and history itself.

programme.title: Comedy Meets Classic
programme.desc: Created by British comedy duo Carrington-Brown, based in Berlin, and Irish conductor ClA�odhna NA� AodA�in, based in Switzerland. They join forces with "The Swonderful Orchestra" for this exciting, classy, and hilarious music & comedy show.

programme.title: Flirting With Flamenco
programme.desc: When Sylvia's well-meaning dad (Watt) surprises her with a devastating revelation, Sylvia's world is turned upside down. But will she crumble or prove herself at the local flamenco contest? An uplifting feel-good Brit comedy drama, Flirting with Flamenco will have you laughing, crying and feeling empowered to turn your life around.

programme.title: The Flying Deuces
programme.desc: When two bumbling friends join the French Foreign Legion on a whim, they find themselves in a whirlwind of misadventures, love, and laughter as they attempt to navigate the challenges of military life in a foreign land.

programme.title: Perfect Girl
programme.desc: A coming of age romance for anyone who's ever had a crush. Since high school, Stan and Jenny have had crushes on each other. They wrote letters to one another over school holidays but in person they barely spoke; sharing only the occasional lingering glance and smile. Over the years they fantasized about how perfect they would be as lovers. Ten years later they bump into each other and have the chance to make it a reality, but it's not that simple; self doubt, fear of rejection, of losing their fantasies will hold them back from what could be the perfect union.

programme.title: I Would Have Kissed You
programme.desc: Three months after college graduation, best friends Mattie and Olivia are struggling to write a feature and struggling even more with their love lives. Mattie finds herself in a grey area with her college ex-boyfriend while Olivia clings to the hope that her crush will finally want to be with her (despite his hot new girlfriend.) British Web Awards - Awarded "Best Writing in a Dramedy" and "Best Music" Top Indie Awards -Awarded "Best Humor" WRPN Women's International Film Festival - Awarded "Exceptional Merit Award"

programme.title: The General
programme.desc: When Union spies steal Johnnie Gray's (Buster Keaton) beloved locomotive, the General, he pursues them with the aid of his fiance, Annabelle Lee (Marion Mack) straight through enemy lines. One of the most revered comedies of the silent era.

programme.title: Finding Joy
programme.desc: A struggling writer rediscovers himself, his offbeat family, and what it means to be happy when he meets Joy – a spirited, possibly-dying young woman who asks him to write her obituary.

programme.title: Brazzy Jazzy
programme.desc: When a Brazilian Girl takes on the NYC fashion world, her adventures are sometimes sexy, often funny but always Caffeinated! It's Jane the Virgin meets Girls, only an outsider immigrant version - more like Girls of the 3rd World.

programme.title: Growing Op
programme.desc: In an average American neighborhood, a family of four breaks all conformity making it difficult for their 18 year old son to fit in to society.

programme.title: 30 Nights of Sex

programme.title: ChatRoom - Credit Card Debt

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Detroit
programme.desc: Our visit to the motor city begins with a brisk workout overlooking a spectacular view of nearby Windsor Ontario Canada then we take to the ropes course at Joe Dumars Fieldhouse. On day two we take an interactive trip through history at the Charles H. Wright museum and visit the Federal Reserve Bank to see where old money goes to die. On day three we stop by the Detroit Zoo to serve up some treats to the polar bears and we check out the Henry Ford museum where the model T still runs like a top. We wrap up our visit to Detroit with a stop at the Cranbrook Science Institute and stop by Motown’s world famous studio A which produced some of the greatest hits in music history.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - South Africa
programme.desc: This week we’ll travel to the beautiful country of South Africa where we first get to see many different exotic animals. Next, we’ll set out on foot to find more fascinating wildlife. Then, we’ll get a lesson in survival skills from a trained African guide. Our trip ends with a surprise visit from an elephant on this fun-filled episode of “Awesome Adventures.”

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - New Zealand
programme.desc: This week we traveled to the beautiful country of New Zealand.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Ding Darling
programme.desc: In this show, we visit the Ding Darling Wildlife Refuge in Florida that serves as home to many exotic birds like the roseate spoonbill, reddish egret and white ibis. Then we travel to Africa where you'll see a cheetah in action and elephants, lions and hippopotamuses in their natural habitat. In Arizona, we'll take you to a special area where thousands of sandhill cranes create a spectacle when they fill the skies every morning. And we'll visit a bayou in Louisiana where alligators, green tree frogs and diamondback water snakes inhabit this unique area.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Wolf Lady
programme.desc: Today’s show on “Wild About Animals” features fascinating stories. First we visit the “Wolf Lady,” a former model who cares for wolves. Next our show features a 3 month-old kangaroo rescued from her dead mother and raised by a caring animal lover. The joey survived for 12 months before breaking her leg. Finally, “Wild About Animals” travels to the Camden Aquarium for a look at sharks, poisonous fish, and beautiful marine life. It is truly an eye opening experience.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Ocean Creatures
programme.desc: Join Emmy Award-winning Actress, Mariette Hartley, as she travels the globe to bring viewers fascinating stories!

programme.title: Whaddyado - BuffaloAttacks
programme.desc: A wild buffalo attacks a spectator at a famous National Park...a tornado hits a busy airport and the passengers need to run for cover...a mother is choking on a piece of steak and her 13 year old daughter must save her...after a high speed chase, a police officer discovers that the reckless driver is only 12 years old...our Moral Dilemma looks at the recent fad of romantic neck biting, an affection that can lead to an infection.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Car Crash
programme.desc: A 13 year old boy is choking on a school bus and thankfully the bus driver knows just what to do. * There’s a bad car crash on multi-lane highway that leads to another crash – what precautions should be taken to protect you and others. * Skateboarding is a popular sport with teenagers but they need to have the correct equipment. * Avalanches are a deadly winter adversary…what do you do if you’re caught up in one…watch.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Hand in Engine
programme.desc: With his hand caught in a boat engine, a man must rely on his teenage passenger for help. * A young man witnesses an accident and must put his newly acquired CPR skills to the test. * Plus, a moral dilemma segment looks at the disturbing subject of dating violence.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Break Up
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: The relationship has run its course – no comes the hard part – breaking up. And we sink our teeth into the growing problem of childhood obesity.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Internet Gambling
programme.desc: This week’s topics include: A nip here and a tuck there, in your teens? And, Internet gambling, are the odds really in your favor? If teens are thinking about it or feeling it, we’re discussing it, in the ChatRoom.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Bad Mother
programme.desc: This week’s topics include: He seems familiar, but will he take them for a ride? And Mom makes an offer that could change the whole party. Is she a cool mom or a poor parent? If teens are thinking about it or feeling it, we’re discussing it, in the ChatRoom.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Bahamas
programme.desc: On this adventure, we’ll soak up some rays in the beautiful Bahamas. First we’ll try some water slides. Then we’ll take a look at the water underneath the surface with personal submarines. We’ll even get an up close look at some sharks beneath the sea. Finally, we’ll end our trip with a great ride on some wave runners.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Best of 98
programme.desc: On this week’s episode of “Awesome Adventures’ we will highlight the most exciting & educational Awesome Adventures featured from our 1998/99 season. Highlights feature adventures from Iceland, Hawaii, Belize and many other countries.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - SoCal
programme.desc: This week it's off to the sunshine of Southern California.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Capuchin Monkeys
programme.desc: This episode of “Wild About Animals,” features capuchin monkeys. Following that, we go backstage at the Westminster Dog Show in Madison Square Garden in New York City to find out what it takes to prepare these dogs for show time! Plus we’ll examine the puffer fish - a Japanese delicacy that could kill you. And we’ll travel to the Serengeti in Africa to learn the disturbing story of a disease, which has killed more than 1,000 African lions.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Santa Barbara Zoo
programme.desc: This week on Wild About Animals we see how one Giraffe united an entire staff together. We visit primates in Texas, who were raised by humans and now must learn what it means to be a monkey. Then we stop by the Santa Barbara Zoo where one penguin really knows how to accessorize. Finally we follow one couple on their noble journey of dog adoption.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - New Zealand
programme.desc: This week on Wild About Animals we travel to New Zealand. We stop by the Auckland Zoo and see how a group of rescued fur seals are helping educate the community about their species. We then head to the caves where one insect helps light the way for everyone who comes through. Later we take a look at the sheep shearing industry.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Saving Pet
programme.desc: A 16-year-old teenager is struck by lightning and still survives. We’ll tell you what you should do if you find someone struck by lightning. *A dog trainer saves a dog’s life by giving it CPR. We’ll show you how to give CPR to help save your pet. * When a family’s car is stuck in the snow, they nearly die of carbon monoxide poisoning. We‘ll explain how carbon monoxide is the invisible killer and can be avoided. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the growing trend of sexual harassment at work.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Avalanche
programme.desc: A snowmobile rider goes mountain climbing and starts an avalanche. * We revisit the Mount St. Helen eruption site and hear from those who survived the volcano. * A house boat gets stuck on a dam on the Kentucky River. * A woman kayaker is pinned against a rock in a rapid. Will she survive?

programme.title: Whaddyado - Mountain Biker Falls
programme.desc: While fishing, a mother and her three sons get stuck on a river bank during a flashflood.* A mountain biker falls 200 feet down a steep jagged cliff-he’s ok, but what precautions should have been taken. *A horse is stuck in a frozen pond and a man is stuck in a pine tree 70 feet off the ground trying to save a pet…whaddyado?

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Factor Fiction
programme.desc: This episode examines some of the popular notions surrounding the Apollo program and discerns whether they are fact or fiction. Did President Kennedy try to work together with the Soviet Union to get a man on the moon? These and more are featured in Fact or Fiction.

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Amiable Strangers
programme.desc: Three very different, uniquely talented men came together to form the crew of Apollo 11. Neil Armstrong, the skilled pilot, Buzz Aldrin, the astronaut with a PhD, and Mike Collins, the well-liked pilot of the command module. This episode looks at all three men, not only in their professional capacities, but their personalities as well. They were, as Mike Collins described them, “amiable strangers.”

programme.title: The Apollo Chronicles - Part 3 - Failure And Fire

On the following days, we’ll go horseback riding through the country side, visit a steaming hot spring, and venture to Vatnajokull, the third largest glacier in the world.

He said, “As we leave the moon, we leave as we came and God willing as we shall return. ”But with Nasa relying on government funding, the path back to the moon has been full of obstacles. This episode examines how each new President has their own vision of space exploration, and why this results in stops and starts in the space program.

programme.title: Xploration Outer Space - Moon to Mars
programme.desc: The moon is the next logical starting point for deep space exploration, and the Artemis missions are headed there. But there are those who think it is a mistake to focus on our closet celestial neighbor. They say we should get to Mars, and once there, turn it into a living planet. The debate rages…on Xploration Outer Space.

programme.title: Stuart Cooper Films - The Craig Jones Story
programme.desc:
A short documentary telling the story of Craig Jones' sudden rise to success after his upset victory over Leandro Lo at ADCC 2017. After his breakout performance at ADCC, Craig went on to beat many more big names such as Jake Shields In Polaris, and made it to the finals of EBI, where he had a close finals match against Gordon Ryan. Since then Craig has competed in some of the biggest tournaments in the world and his life has changed dramatically. In this film we see that it wasn't always an easy road for him.
Director Stuart Cooper

programme.title: Superfight - Andre Galvao vs Braulio Estima by Stuart Cooper
programme.desc: In this video Andre Galvao looks back on his match with Braulio Estima for the ADCC 2013 Super Fight Title. Then, Andre recaps on some of his most entertaining matches from ADCC 2011, which include; Don Ortega, Gunnar Nelson, Pablo Popovitch, Rousimar "Toquinho" Palhares and Sergio Moraes.

programme.title: Tap Out Challenge - Oceanside
programme.desc: On October 15th at the picturesque Oceanside, CA, Charles Rials embarked on an incredible BJJ journey, challenging strangers from all walks of life to tap me out and claim $100. But there was a twist that none of them saw coming! Win or Lose, they got the MONEY!!! What they all shared was the courage to step up, the passion to engage, and the heart of a warrior. This video isn't just about BJJ or the challenge — it's a celebration of the human spirit, perseverance, and the unexpected twists that life (and jiu jitsu) can throw our way. Join Charles in this heartwarming, adrenaline-pumping journey where every challenge was met with respect, and every challenger was met with a surprise. Whether you're a BJJ enthusiast or someone who loves to witness genuine human moments, this video has something special for you.

programme.title: ADCC - Denver Opens
programme.desc: The Opens make their way to the mile high city where the best martial arts from the US look to stake their claim for supremacy as the circuit heats up. In this heart-pounding instalment, we bring you all the action from the epic showdown held in the magnificent city of Denver. Former UFC Strawweight Champion of the World Rose Namajunas known for her exceptional martial arts abilities, Rose is now ready to put her skills to the ultimate test in the realm of grappling. Witness her transition from the cage to the mats, as she grapples her way through some of the most intense matches of her career. programme.title: The New Wave of Stand-Up - The New Wave of Stand-Up: Matty Vu
programme.desc: Matty Vu is the bad boy of Vancouver's comedy scene, pushing the limits of audiences all over. Ok, he's just a nice boy who does comedy. He's also a 30-something man who still calls himself a boy.

programme.title: The New Wave of Stand-Up - The New Wave of Stand-Up: Paul Rabliauskas
programme.desc: Paul Rabliauskas hails from Poplar River First Nation. He’s been performing for over a decade and has been a regular on the CBC’s Debaters, was featured on the JFL’s Homegrown showcase in 2018 and has performed a handful of times in the Winnipeg comedy festival. Paul's charming, brash, and boisterous style makes him a fan favorite of so many across Canada.

programme.title: The New Wave of Stand-Up - The New Wave of Stand-Up: Yumi Nagashima
programme.desc: Yumi Nagashima’s career trajectory has seen a meteoric rise in the past two years. Her accomplishments in include: a YouTube channel that has exploded in popularity; releasing her debut Album “My Name Is Yumi” on 604 Records; recording a Comedy Central Asia Special; and appearances at top comedy festivals including Just for Laughs’ New Faces Showcase.

programme.title: The New Wave of Stand-Up - The New Wave of Stand-Up: Allie Pearse
programme.desc: Allie Pearse is a writer on the award winning show Letterkenny and the 2021 winner of JFL’s Standup & Pitch competition.

programme.title: The New Wave of Stand-Up - The New Wave of Stand-Up: Brett Forte
programme.desc: Brett Forte was born in 92’ but we’re pretty sure he grew up in the 80’s. He’s embarrassed by his generation and thinks you should be too.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: Will Forte: The Time of Your Time
programme.desc: Saturday Night Live alumni and star of The Last Man on Earth, Will Forte, comes to Montreal to host one night of uproariously funny stand-up comedy in a special that can’t be missed. Featuring stand-out performances by Dylan Moran, Mario Joyner, Maria Bamford, Adam Christie, Cameron Esposito and Trent McClellan.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: - Cheech & Chong : Puff Puff Laugh
programme.desc: The inventors of stoner comedy, legends Cheech & Chong are still jokin’ (and possibly smokin’). Catch them as they perform some of their funniest bits, recall some hilarious behind-the-scenes stories from their days of filming ‘Up In Smoke’ and host a full bag of the world’s funniest comedians. Included in the special are Last Comic Standing finalist Lavell Crawford, creator and star of the Brit cult comedy The Mighty Boosh Noel Fielding, the ever-opinionated Bill Burr, and Canada’s own rising star Jay Malone.

programme.title: Decline of the American Empire
programme.desc: Hosted by The Daily Show’s favourite Brit correspondent John Oliver, The Decline of the American Empire is the comedy dissection of our neighbours to the South… sort of a hilarious outsider’s State of the Union. It’s the smartest, most opinionated and politically-fuelled show in the lineup show, so get ready to piss your political trousers, speak your mind and have a look at the future, or lack thereof, of the USA.

programme.title: Night of One Million Opinions
programme.desc: Never the introvert, the Angriest Man in America Lewis Black hosts a roster of opinionated comics who just want to be heard, dammit! Along with Lewis spewing his usual bile about the state of everything, Derek Edwards pontificates on his driving frustrations, Dom Irrera thinks alcohol is wonderful, Kathleen Madigan has lost all hope for America, Greg Giraldo rants on about how women have all the power today, and Paul F Tompkins has probably the most incendiary topic of all. You’d be an idiot to miss it… then again, that’s just our opinion.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: - Chris Lockee: Captain Bones
programme.desc: Chris Locke brings his personal brand of offbeat humour to the stages of Montreal for one night of laugh-out-loud comedy. From from chip flavours and sausage roles, to kids brains and vasectomies, nothing is off the table in this new half-hour stand-up special from Just For Laughs.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: - Chris Robinson: Panning for Gold
programme.desc: From puppies and 4-year olds, to porn ads and fishnets, nothing and no-one is off-limits for Chris Robinson in this hilarious new stand-up comedy special from Just For Laughs.

programme.desc: Jason has attempted to climb the Grand Teton, located in Wyoming, three times before the couple's adventure out west. Will the fourth time be a charm? Or will life's unplanned moments present even greater challenges than Jason anticipated?

programme.desc: Paddle into Dog Surfing in Pacifica, California, and get picking at the Crab Derby in Crisfield, Maryland.

programme.title: Beach Battles - Beach Battles: Winchester Bay & Long Beach
programme.desc: High-octane dune racing in Winchester Bay, Oregon, plus high-flying Kitefest fun in Long Beach, Washington.

programme.title: Beach Battles - Beach Battles: Key West & Wrightsville
programme.desc: Dive into the fun blowing conchs in Key West, Florida and race pro SUPS in Wrightsville Beach, North Carolina.

programme.desc: The next stop on Sorted Food's Epic Southern Road Trip is Savannah, Georgia. Will the guys be able to learn enough in such a short period of time?

programme.title: Epic Southern Road Trip - Savannah Part 2
programme.desc: After exploring Savannah, Georgia for 48 hours learning the ropes of Southern food and hospitality, Chef Ben, Jamie and Mike try hosting a dinner party for local chefs, food writers and Savannah natives. How will these expectant locals react?

programme.title: Sorted Food: Game Changers - Puerto Rico Street Food Face Off

programme.title: Epic Trails - Epic Trails: Backpacking West Virginia

programme.title: One Perfect Day in Kentucky - One Perfect Day in Kentucky
programme.desc: In "One Perfect Day in Kentucky," BFF’s Kimberly and Elsa bring their shared competitive streak to the Bluegrass State, facing off to find out who can plan the perfect Kentucky day. Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. Elsa wins the first point, but Kimberly’s ready to up the ante, whisking Elsa away for a thrilling cave kayaking adventure at the Gorge Underground. As they ride the chairlift to the top of the stunning Natural Bridge, the rivalry kicks into high gear and they go head-to-head in a trivia battle. The next surprise – a toast with Kentucky’s own Ale-8 soda , sourced by Kimberly straight from the factory only whets their whistles. At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. At Louisville’s Trouble Bar, Kimberly shares her newfound knowledge of Kentucky bourbon production from a tour and tasting at Castle + Key distillery and makes Elsa One Perfect Drink.

programme.title: Adventure Cities - Adventure Cities
programme.desc: Jonathan Thompson explores the adventurous side of St. Petersburg Clearwater, Florida; Charleston, South Carolina; and Juneau, Alaska.

programme.title: America's Musical Journey - America's Musical Journey
programme.desc: A cross-country adventure through the musical heritage of America and the cultural cities where America's music was born.

programme.title: USA Through Film - USA Through Film 2
programme.desc: Actor and director Jordan Spiro (Ozark, Night Comes On) spent childhood vacations with her family in New Orleans. For Spiro, the city’s heritage as the birthplace of jazz is reflected in its mélange of arts and food culture that always feels fresh, inviting, and joyous, even after a lifetime of visits. “There’s this ‘all senses on overload’ side to New Orleans that takes my breath away every time.”

programme.title: Small Town, Big Story - Bridge Day

programme.desc: Paul and Nick meet Mary Drymon, who has written about how Scottish and Ulster food traditions have widely influenced how America eats today. We’re on the coast of New England, so expect some lobster to feature…

programme.desc: Paul and Nick cook for friends of the Scots’ Charitable Society, the oldest charity in America, set up to help fund the education of Scots in America. programme.title: Cheat Meal - Cheat Meal: Virginia Beach, Part 1
programme.desc: Tyler and Monica head to Virginia Beach where they’re tasked by celebrity chef Cliff Crooks to create the ultimate cheat meal for a local restaurateur. Armed with the power of their taste buds, the dynamic duo checks out the best places to eat, including Oishii Burger, Chick’s Oyster Bar and Klassic Doughnuts, to build an off-the-charts meal of epic portions.

programme.title: Cheat Meal - Cheat Meal: Virginia Beach, Part 2
programme.desc: Tyler and Monica dive back into Virginia Beach's vibrant food scene to build the ultimate cheat meal for George Culver, the food-loving force behind the popular @iheartfoodvb. From the tropical vibes at Moxy Virginia Beach to the game-filled hangouts at Beachside Social, and the delightful flavors of Oh Mochi, De Rican Chef, and Belvedere South, they pull out all the stops to craft a meal that’s as unforgettable as it is indulgent!

programme.title: Cheat Meal - Cheat Meal: Galveston
programme.desc: Tyler and Monica head to Galveston, Texas, to create a fiery feast for Concetta, the spice-obsessed owner of Maceo Spice & Import Co. From the coastal vibes at Vida Agave to island-famous eats at The Spot, savory classics at Mario’s Seawall, local favorites at Mosquito Cafe, and indulgent sweets from Pattycakes Bakery, they turn up the heat to craft a cheat meal packed with bold flavors and Galveston flair.

They visit the producer of the hottest chili pepper in the world, get a taste for the Carolina peach and find out about the State’s tradition of ‘slow and low’ barbecue.

programme.title: Paul & Nick's Big American Food Trip - Knoxville, Tennessee

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 367 - Up Next Fighting 11 - Middleweight Championship Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 11, the Middleweight Championship, from Southern California. In this episode of UFA, wrestler Armen Piloyan faces striker Diego Perez in a lightweight clash and Steven O'Bryant steps into the cage with Anthony Zaragosa. In the main event challenger Sidiah Parker looks to take the belt from the current champion Curtis Millender. Special guest appearance from the youngest ring annoucer in the world, Cameron Michael "Killer Cam" introduces the main event fighters.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 364 - Bare Knuckle Boxing 34 Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Bare Knuckle Boxing 34 part 1 from London. Up first in a cruiser weight contest, England's Martyn Grainger steps into the ring with Szymon Szynkiewicz of Poland followed by Ryan McCann versus Dean Morris in a featherweight bout. Also John Collier takes on Jonny Lawson with 16 BKB fights under his belt and in a superweight title clash Danylo Hrebenuyk and undefeated Matty Moore touch gloves.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 365 - Bare Knuckle Boxing 34 Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Bare Knuckle Boxing 34 part 2 from London. In this episode Tony Barratt takes on Craig Griffiths in a heavyweight BKB contest, in the women's division Mathilda Wilson faces Lailane Mota in a Swedish versus Brazil clash. Watch as experienced MMA fighter George Hillyard and MMA legend Rolando Gabriel Dy step into the ring while Pat Nash takes on Lee Spencer. With the British Featherweight Title up for grabs, Reece Murray and Martin Reffell battle for the belt. In the main event, Aaron McCallum and Mark Tiffin are set to meet the challenge with the bantamweight title on the line.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 372 - Dynamite Fighting Show 22 Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Dynamite Fighting Show 22 part 1 from Romania. Watch as Andrei Varga "The Bonecrusher" faces Adrian Maxim in a youth versus expierence bout where the winner will move on in the tournament. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 351 - KOK 103 World Series Tallinn Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 103 part 1 from Tallinn, Estonia. Kicking things off tonight Lithuanian Gedminas Justinas takes on Moldova's Sergei Cheles. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 353 - KOK 103 World Series Tallinn Part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 103 part 3 from Tallinn, Estonia. programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents KOK '84 World Series from Vilnius Lithuania part 1. In a battle between Lithuanian fighters, Zygimantas Kidikas making his pro debut goes up against his 2-0 opponent Ovidijus Pocius. Watch as Aleh Moshin (Belarus) faces Samuelis Sorochovas (Lithuania), Osvaladas Fedorovic takes on the less experienced Aurimas Krukauskas in a battle between Lithuanian fighters and Vladislav Shatunskui (Poland) battles against Gustas Dimsa (Lithuania).
